sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    participant FE  as Frontend (React)
    participant GW  as gatewayserver
    participant OS  as orderserver (OrderService)
    participant PD  as productserver (Feign)
    participant ODB as order DB (PostgreSQL)
    participant OOB as order_outbox
    participant DEB as Debezium CDC
    participant K   as Kafka
    participant INV as inventoryserver
    participant PAY as paymentserver
    participant SSE as PaymentSseService
    participant Toss as Toss JS SDK / API

    Note over FE,Toss: [Step 1] Order creation — synchronous HTTP flow

    FE->>GW: POST /orders<br/>Header: X-User-Id: {userId}<br/>Body: { items[{productId, qty, price}] }
    GW->>OS: X-User-Id header + OrderRequest forwarded

    rect rgb(220, 240, 255)
        Note over OS,ODB: @Transactional — single atomic transaction
        OS->>OS: validateOrderRequest() — check items not empty

        OS->>PD: POST /product/checkout/validate (Feign)<br/>{ items[{productId, qty, unitPrice}] }
        PD-->>OS: CheckoutValidationResponse<br/>{ validatedItems[{productId, serverPrice, valid}] }

        OS->>OS: calculateTotalAmount()<br/>client price vs server price integrity check<br/>IllegalArgumentException on mismatch

        OS->>ODB: save Orders<br/>state = ORDER_CHECKED_OUT
        OS->>ODB: save OrderHistory per item (snapshot)
        OS->>OOB: order_outbox INSERT<br/>event_type = OrderCheckedOut<br/>payload = { orderId, userId, items, totalAmount }
    end

    OS-->>GW: 201 Created  { orderId }
    GW-->>FE: 201 Created  { orderId }

    Note over FE,Toss: [Step 2] Toss payment widget — frontend client-side

    FE->>Toss: toss.requestPayment("CARD", {<br/>  orderId, amount, orderName,<br/>  successUrl, failUrl<br/>})
    Note over FE,Toss: User selects payment method and completes authentication in Toss widget

    Toss-->>FE: redirect to successUrl<br/>?paymentKey=...&orderId=...&amount=...

    Note over FE,SSE: [Step 3] Payment confirmation — SSE subscribe then confirm

    FE->>GW: GET /payments/orders/{orderId}/events<br/>(SSE subscription — text/event-stream)
    GW->>PAY: SSE subscribe request
    PAY->>SSE: subscribe(orderId)
    SSE-->>FE: connection established (100ms keepalive heartbeat)

    FE->>GW: POST /payments/confirm<br/>{ paymentKey, orderId, amount }
    GW->>PAY: confirm processing start<br/>(-> payment-confirm-flow)

    Note over PAY,SSE: After 3-phase Toss processing — SSE + HTTP response simultaneously
    PAY->>SSE: publishCompleted / publishFailed
    SSE-->>FE: payment-status event<br/>{ status, approvedAt / failureCode }
    PAY-->>GW: 200 PaymentResponse / 500 error
    GW-->>FE: HTTP response (same result as SSE)

    Note over DEB,PAY: [Async parallel flow] Outbox -> Kafka event chain

    rect rgb(245, 245, 245)
        Note over OOB,PAY: Starts immediately when Debezium CDC detects order_outbox (async)
        DEB->>OOB: order_outbox INSERT detected (CDC polling)
        DEB->>K: OrderCheckedOut topic published

        K->>INV: inventoryserver consumes<br/>reserve inventory (RESERVED)
        INV->>K: PaymentRequested topic published

        K->>PAY: paymentserver consumes<br/>create Payment record (state=READY)<br/>assign idempotencyKey
    end

    Note over PAY,Toss: Payment(READY) record must exist in paymentserver<br/>before confirm request arrives for Phase 1 DB lookup to succeed
